  stimulus_text = 'The following text is adapted from the 1999 novel "The Lovely Bones" by Alice Sebold. The narrator of the novel is Susie Salmon, who is a young girl who has been murdered and is now observing the world from Heaven. Susie is watching her family, especially her father, as they try to move on with their lives after her death. Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
